OF SPECIFIC INTEREST IS THE DEVELOPMENT OF A COMPACT LOW-POWER DIRECT ON-CHIP DIGITAL OPTICAL SYNTHESIZER (DODOS) THAT CONVERTS RF TO OPTICAL FREQUENCY WITH PROGRAMMABLE FREQUENCY RESOLUTION OF ONE PART IN 1014, VOLUME OF<1 CM3, AND POWER CONSUMPTION OF<1WATT. THE MAIN OBJECTIVE OF THE DODOS PROGRAM IS THE DEVELOPMENT OF THE NECESSARY COMPONENT TECHNOLOGIES AND INTEGRATION INTO A ROBUST, COMPACT, LOW-SWAP DEVICE.
